$ Oracle: DBMS_OUTPUT
@ dbms_output

Send messages from stored procedures (poor man's debugging)

{ Procedures

  table { ll
    `disable` ☰
    `enable` ☰
    `get_line` ☰
    `get_lines` ☰
    `get_lines` ☰
    `new_line` ☰
    `put` ☰
    `put_line` ☰
  table }

}

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/pipe[`dbms_pipe`] allows to send messages between two or more sessions.

  → development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms

  → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer#sql-developer-turn-on-dbms_output[Turning on dbms_output in SQL Developer].
  -
  See also the menu → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/GUI/menu/View/Dbms-Output[View -> Dbms Output].

  → Linux/fhs/u01/app/oracle/product/vv-v-v/dbhome_n/rdbms/admin/dbmsotpt_sql[`$ORACLE_HOME/rdbms/admin/dbmsotpt.sql`]

  In order to automatically enable `dbms_output` in → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer[SQL Developer], the value of
  *Filename for connection startup script*, found under the menu → development/Software/Oracle-SQL-Developer/GUI/menu/Tools/Preferences/Database[Tools -> Preferences -> Databases] might
  be set to a script that contains `set serveroutput on`.

  → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath/outon[`outon.sql`] is a most simple SQL script to be put into a → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus/sqlpath[`$SQLPATH` directory]. It «enables»
 `dbms_output` in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus.
